message.content: Before Cam broke his right arm, he could type approximately 45 words (9 wpm x 5 minutes) in 5 minutes on his phone. After breaking his arm and having to use his left hand, he could only type approximately 30 words (6 wpm x 5 minutes) in the same amount of time. Therefore, there is a difference of 15 words per minute (45 words - 30 words) between the number of words Cam could type in 5 minutes before and after breaking his arm.
